[SN]TITLE[SN]
Wrexham Maelor Hospital wards shut due to norovirus

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Five wards at Wrexham Maelor Hospital have been closed to the public following an outbreak of norovirus.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Two other wards also have some restrictions in place in a bid to stop it spreading.
The move comes after 21 patients showed symptoms of the winter vomiting bug.
A Betsi Cadwaladr health board spokesman urged any visitors with symptoms to stay away from the hospital.
